  "prompt": "If your direct customer cohort is not on Facebook (specially in B2B), how do you steer that social channel to pull in audiences for your business?",
  "response": "Here are strategic approaches to leverage Facebook for B2B audience engagement even when your direct customer cohort isn't actively present:\n\n1. Targeting Strategies\n- Target decision-makers through:\n- Job title targeting\n- Industry-specific interest targeting\n- Company size demographics\n- Professional interest categories\n\n2. Content Approach\n- Share thought leadership content\n- Post industry insights\n- Create educational video content\n- Showcase case studies\n- Highlight employee expertise\n- Share behind-the-scenes company culture\n\n3. Audience Expansion\n- Use lookalike audiences\n- Retarget website visitors\n- Create custom audiences from LinkedIn/email lists\n- Leverage professional networking groups\n\n4. Advertising Techniques\n- Use precise audience segmentation\n- Create lead generation ads\n- Develop lead magnets (whitepapers, webinars)\n- Implement conversion-focused campaigns\n\n5. Indirect Engagement\n- Share content that attracts adjacent professionals\n- Build brand awareness\n- Create shareable, professional content\n- Use LinkedIn integration strategies\n\n6. Complementary Platforms\n- Cross-promote content on LinkedIn\n- Use Facebook as supplementary channel\n- Drive traffic to more professional platforms\n\n7. Measurement\n- Track engagement metrics\n- Monitor lead quality\n- Analyze conversion rates\n- Adjust targeting continuously",
